parameters.name: SC_POT
parameters.description: [SC_POT] Spacecraft potential estimated from electron ONLY measurements

parameters.name: SC_CURRENT
parameters.description: ---> [SC_CURRENT?] Current contribution to the spacecraft from thermal electrons

parameters.name: MAGF
parameters.description: ---> [MAGF] magnetic field vector interpolated (linearly) to the time of the EESA Low distribution, in GSE cartesian components

parameters.name: FLUX
parameters.description: ---> [FLUX] electron total number flux - cartesian GSE

parameters.name: PTENS
parameters.description: [PTENS] electron Pressure Tensor calculated in the GSE coordinate basis.  The elements correspond to, in the following order: XX, YY, ZZ, XY, XZ, YZ

parameters.name: MFTENS
parameters.description: ---> [MFTENS] electron Momentum Flux Tensor calculated in the GSE coordinate basis.  The elements correspond to, in the following order: XX, YY, ZZ, XY, XZ, YZ

parameters.name: T3
parameters.description: ---> [T3] electron Temperature eigenvalues after diagonalization of tensor, calculated in the GSE coordinate basis.  The elements correspond to:  XX, YY, ZZ

parameters.name: SYMM
parameters.description: [SYMM] ZZ-component of the eigenvectors associated with the eigen values from the diagonalized .T3 (i.e., the eigenvector associated with the Z eigen value from .T3 or .T3[2])

parameters.name: SYMM_ANG
parameters.description: ---> [SYMM_ANG] angle between the ZZ-component of the eigenvectors associated with the eigen values from the diagonalized .T3 and the magnetic field vector (i.e., .MAGF vector)

parameters.name: MAGT3
parameters.description: ---> [MAGT3] electron temperature tensor... rotated into a field-aligned coordinate basis and then taking the diagonal elements only

parameters.name: ERANGE
parameters.description: [P.ERANGE] electron energy range used to compute the moments
